---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About IsItAuDHD.com — free quizzes and resources for understanding the autism and ADHD overlap."
>
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-text mb-8">About IsItAuDHD</h1>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-text-light text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        <strong class="text-text">IsItAuDHD</strong> exists because understanding yourself
        shouldn't cost hundreds of dollars or require a year-long waiting list.
      </p>

      <p>
        If you've ever felt like the advice for ADHD doesn't quite fit, or the descriptions
        of autism don't fully capture your experience, you might be one of the many people
        living at the intersection of both. That intersection has a name:
        <strong class="text-text">AuDHD</strong>.
      </p>

      <p>
        We built this site to give people a starting point — a way to explore traits,
        learn about the overlap, and figure out whether seeking a formal assessment
        might be worthwhile. Our quizzes are free, private, and designed with
        neurodivergent brains in mind.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-surface rounded-[--radius-xl] p-6 border border-border">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text mb-4">What We Believe</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary flex-shrink-0">•</span>
            <span>Self-understanding is valuable, even without a formal diagnosis</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary flex-shrink-0">•</span>
            <span>Neurodivergence is a difference, not a deficit</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary flex-shrink-0">•</span>
            <span>Information about your own brain should be free and accessible</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary flex-shrink-0">•</span>
            <span>Websites should be designed for the people who use them — including neurodivergent people</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text mb-3">A Note on Our Quizzes</h2>
        <p>
          Our quizzes are research-informed but not clinical instruments. They're designed to
          help you explore patterns in your experiences. They cannot tell you whether you
          are autistic, have ADHD, or have both — only a qualified professional can do that.
          What they <em>can</em> do is help you put words to experiences you may have
          struggled to articulate, and give you a framework for conversations with
          professionals or with yourself.
        </p>
      </div>

      <p>
        If you have feedback, suggestions, or just want to say hi, reach out at
        <strong class="text-text">hello@isitaudhd.com</strong>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
